references.name: Alpaca Expeditions - Classic Inca Trail Trek

routeIdea:
My idea is a route for "The Inca Trail to Machu Picchu", which is real world.
The  pitch for this route is "Follow the ancient paths of the Incas through the Andes mountains, culminating in the breathtaking ruins of Machu Picchu. This historic trek offers a glimpse into the past with its well-preserved archaeological sites.".
Some ideas for steps are: 
	 - Cusco to Ollantaytambo
	 - Ollantaytambo to Wayllabamba
	 - Wayllabamba to Pacaymayo
	 - Pacaymayo to Wiñay Wayna
	 - Wiñay Wayna to Machu Picchu

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Begin your journey in Cusco, the historic capital of the Inca Empire, where you can acclimatize to the altitude and prepare for the trek.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Travel to Ollantaytambo, a charming town with impressive Incan ruins and a vibrant local market.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Cusco is a well-known city in Peru, accessible by air and road.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Depart from Ollantaytambo, known for its well-preserved Incan architecture.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Reach Wayllabamba, the first campsite on the Inca Trail, surrounded by lush greenery.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Ollantaytambo is a popular starting point for the Inca Trail, accessible by train or road.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Start your trek from Wayllabamba, enjoying the scenic views of the Andes.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Arrive at Pacaymayo, a campsite offering stunning views of the surrounding mountains.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Wayllabamba is a known campsite on the Inca Trail, marked on most trekking maps.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Depart from Pacaymayo, continuing your journey through diverse ecosystems.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Reach Wiñay Wayna, a beautiful archaeological site and your last campsite before Machu Picchu.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Pacaymayo is a common stop on the Inca Trail, known for its scenic beauty.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Begin your final day at Wiñay Wayna, where you will prepare for the last leg of the trek.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Reach Machu Picchu through the Sun Gate, where you will be greeted with breathtaking views of the ancient city.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Wiñay Wayna is a well-known archaeological site on the Inca Trail, marked on most maps.
